com.neovisionaries.bluetooth.ble.advertising

Class ADPayloadParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.neovisionaries.bluetooth.ble.advertising.ADPayloadParser

  • public class ADPayloadParser
extends Object
    Utility to parse a payload of an advertising packet. Especially, the third argument of onLeScan method of android.bluetooth.BluetoothAdapter.LeScanCallback interface. 
     public void onLeScan(BluetoothDevice device, int rssi, byte[] scanRecord)
 {
     List<ADStructure> structures = ADPayloadParser.getInstance().parse(scanRecord);
    Author:
    Takahiko Kawasaki

      • registerBuilder

        public void registerBuilder(int type,
                            ADStructureBuilder builder)
        Register an AD structure builder for the AD type. The given builder is added at the beginning of the list of the builders for the AD type.

        Note that a builder for the type Manufacturer Specific Data (0xFF) should not be registered by this method. Instead, use registerManufacturerSpecificBuilder(int, ADManufacturerSpecificBuilder).

        Parameters:
        type - AD type. The value must be in the range from 0 to 0xFF.
        builder - AD structure builder.

      • registerManufacturerSpecificBuilder

        public void registerManufacturerSpecificBuilder(int companyId,
                                                ADManufacturerSpecificBuilder builder)
        Register a builder for the company ID. The given builder is added at the beginning of the list of the builders for the company ID.
        Parameters:
        companyId - Company ID. The value must be in the range from 0 to 0xFFFF.
        builder - A builder.

      • parse

        public List<ADStructure> parse(byte[] payload,
                               int offset,
                               int length)
        Parse a byte sequence as a list of AD structures.

        Supported AD structures are as follows.

        Data Type Value Data Type Name Class
        0x01 Flags ADFlags
        0x02 Incomplete List of 16-bit Service Class UUIDs ADUUIDs
        0x03 Complete List of 16-bit Service Class UUIDs ADUUIDs
        0x04 Incomplete List of 32-bit Service Class UUIDs ADUUIDs
        0x05 Complete List of 32-bit Service Class UUIDs ADUUIDs
        0x06 Incomplete List of 128-bit Service Class UUIDs ADUUIDs
        0x07 Complete List of 128-bit Service Class UUIDs ADUUIDs
        0x14 List of 16-bit Service Solicitation UUIDs ADUUIDs
        0x15 List of 128-bit Service Solicitation UUIDs ADUUIDs
        0x1F List of 32-bit Service Solicitation UUIDs ADUUIDs
        0xFF Manufacturer Specific Data ADManufacturerSpecific

        In addition, some specific Manufacturer Specific Data are supported.

        Data Type Value Company ID Company Name Format Class
        0xFF 0x004C Apple, Inc. iBeacon IBeacon
        0xFF 0x0105 Ubiquitous Computing Technology Corporation ucode Ucode
        0xFF 0x019A T-Engine Forum ucode Ucode

        registerBuilder and registerManufacturerSpecificBuilder can be used to register your customized parsers for AD structures.

        Parameters:
        payload - A byte array containing of AD structures.
        offset - The offset from which parsing should be started.
        length - The length of bytes to be parsed.
        Returns:
        A list of parsed AD structures. If payload is null, this method returns null.
